1
00:01:09,700 --> 00:01:14,700
"Love Like a Bike"
(Episode 1)

2
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:49,960
Excuse me, where does this path go?

3
00:01:50,600 --> 00:01:51,600
Get off me.

4
00:01:52,480 --> 00:01:53,800
Don't touch me!

5
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:55,840
Are you okay?

6
00:01:56,320 --> 00:01:57,480
Are you okay?

7
00:01:59,040 --> 00:02:02,080
What's with the attitude?

8
00:02:03,960 --> 00:02:05,120
Watch out!

9
00:02:30,080 --> 00:02:31,200
Get away from me!

10
00:02:36,520 --> 00:02:38,120
Mister? Are you alright?

11
00:02:38,320 --> 00:02:39,320
Don't touch me!

12
00:02:39,840 --> 00:02:42,080
Please calm down. I just...

13
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:43,200
Go away!

14
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:50,120
Where is he?

15
00:02:55,840 --> 00:02:57,640
Sailom, what's wrong?

16
00:02:57,800 --> 00:02:59,080
You don't look well.

17
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:02,880
I was hit by a bicycle.

18
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:04,560
What?! Hit by a bicycle?!

19
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:07,560
Damn, are you alright?

20
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:11,680
I'm fine. Don't worry.

21
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:13,560
Are you sure?

22
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:22,800
Oh, no!

23
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:23,840
What's wrong?

24
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,000
My…

25
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:26,800
necklace…

26
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:28,200
My necklace's gone!

27
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:39,800
I've found it!

28
00:03:42,880 --> 00:03:44,080
Is this yours?

29
00:03:49,920 --> 00:03:52,160
James, look at it.

30
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:54,160
Would he wear something like that?

31
00:03:57,280 --> 00:04:00,400
Hey, we've been searching
for some time now.

32
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:02,560
Did the one who hit you take it?

33
00:04:02,920 --> 00:04:04,920
Yeah, what does he look like?

34
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:09,160
Watch out!

35
00:04:10,760 --> 00:04:11,920
He's a man.

36
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:16,120
Quite handsome.

37
00:04:18,080 --> 00:04:22,120
Not like that. Remember what makes
him stand out? Something like…

38
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:23,520
protruding ears,

39
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:26,160
big eyes,

40
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:30,280
or small eyes?

41
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:32,160
Yes, I can remember!

42
00:04:34,760 --> 00:04:35,920
Bicycle!

43
00:04:38,880 --> 00:04:42,840
He rides a bicycle,
wearing a tight cycling suit!

44
00:04:44,120 --> 00:04:45,360
Dude…

45
00:04:45,840 --> 00:04:47,600
Most people ride bicycles in Pattaya.

46
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:51,440
Yep.

47
00:04:52,840 --> 00:04:53,840
So, what's next?

48
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:15,760
Where is that doctor who treated my wife?!

49
00:05:16,320 --> 00:05:17,880
- Please calm down, sir.
- Where is he?!

50
00:05:21,080 --> 00:05:22,080
I'll talk to him.

51
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:27,400
Damn you! Did you tell
Duean to break up with me?!

52
00:05:27,880 --> 00:05:29,320
Mr. Kong, please calm yourself down.

53
00:05:29,440 --> 00:05:34,439
Why must I?! My wife has been
arguing with me since she met you!

54
00:05:34,440 --> 00:05:36,920
I think you told her to break up with me!

55
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:39,000
That's the patient's decision.

56
00:05:40,640 --> 00:05:41,640
Mr. Kong,

57
00:05:42,840 --> 00:05:48,800
I want you to listen what she really wants.
You both might understand each other better.

58
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:51,360
Believe me.

59
00:06:04,440 --> 00:06:06,320
Are you okay?

60
00:06:06,520 --> 00:06:07,760
I'm fine.

61
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:13,320
We're sorry for what happened.

62
00:06:15,960 --> 00:06:21,960
Are you all okay? It's been
a tough day, but we'll get through it.

63
00:06:23,280 --> 00:06:24,280
Do your best.

64
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:35,560
Isn't there any cake today?

65
00:06:36,760 --> 00:06:40,840
Our baker recently
quit. We're really sorry.

66
00:06:41,280 --> 00:06:46,040
Then I'll have coffee.
One hot Americano. Less sweet.

67
00:06:46,280 --> 00:06:47,320
Certainly.

68
00:06:47,960 --> 00:06:49,960
Hot Americano. Less sweet.

69
00:06:50,440 --> 00:06:52,320
- I'll bring it over to your table.
- Thank you.

70
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:07,120
Did Nabnueng put the ring here, sweety?

71
00:07:07,520 --> 00:07:12,840
Yes, Mom. He said he forgot the ring
around here, but I haven't found it.

72
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:15,360
Yeah, it's taking you a while.

73
00:07:16,160 --> 00:07:17,680
Have you checked between the cushions?

74
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:27,920
Mom,

75
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:31,200
have you found it?

76
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:34,080
No, dear. Where did you put it?

77
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:36,800
I really don't know.

78
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:40,680
It isn't in my car or the bathroom.

79
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:45,040
Bro, I couldn't find it. What should we do?

80
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:47,800
It's okay if you can't find it, Looksoh.

81
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:53,760
Or… did you put it in your backpack?

82
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:56,280
Nope, I already checked it.

83
00:07:56,520 --> 00:07:57,840
Maybe you missed somewhere.

84
00:08:03,680 --> 00:08:05,760
Huh? What's this…

85
00:08:06,520 --> 00:08:07,760
necklace?

86
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:11,560
Did you buy it for Yanin?

87
00:08:12,080 --> 00:08:14,560
It's beautiful. Better than the ring.

88
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:18,040
Go for it, bro.
Yanin's gonna accept your proposal.

89
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:44,280
Thank you for remembering
I wanted to try this place.

90
00:08:50,920 --> 00:08:53,000
- I have something to say.
- I have something to say.

91
00:08:55,640 --> 00:08:56,640
Go ahead.

92
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:11,680
How long have we been together?

93
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:14,360
It's been a long time.

94
00:09:15,920 --> 00:09:17,080
Since our student days.

95
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:23,720
I have something to say.

96
00:09:34,680 --> 00:09:36,680
Consider it as bad luck.

97
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:40,600
But that necklace is expensive!
My mom gave it to me!

98
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:44,160
Relax. At least you weren't hurt.

99
00:09:44,520 --> 00:09:45,520
This isn't good at all!

100
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:48,160
Come, let's have a toast.

101
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:10,240
Mister? Are you alright?

102
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:11,320
Don't touch me!

103
00:10:11,640 --> 00:10:12,840
Please calm down. I just...

104
00:10:12,920 --> 00:10:13,920
Go away!

105
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:31,360
Wait! That's my necklace.

106
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:32,880
Huh? Where?

107
00:10:34,920 --> 00:10:36,880
Lemon. James. Call security for me.

108
00:10:43,280 --> 00:10:45,400
You thief! Give it back!

109
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:47,000
Thief?

110
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:49,160
Please mind your language.

111
00:10:49,280 --> 00:10:50,360
That necklace in your hand!

112
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:52,600
This necklace?

113
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:54,600
I saw you dropped it when we collided.

114
00:10:55,720 --> 00:10:56,880
So, I took it.

115
00:10:57,880 --> 00:11:01,800
I see. You admit you took it.

116
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:04,320
What? Wait, wait.

117
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:09,720
This is going too far. I shouted
for you, but you just ran away.

118
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:12,160
So, I kept it to return it to you.

119
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:13,440
So what?

120
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:16,120
Why didn't you give it to the police?

121
00:11:22,120 --> 00:11:23,360
Just know that I'm not a thief.

122
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:25,600
Give my necklace back.

123
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:39,600
I'm returning it to you, and that's it.

124
00:11:50,760 --> 00:11:52,000
Is there a problem here?

125
00:11:56,920 --> 00:11:57,920
Don't touch me.

126
00:11:58,560 --> 00:11:59,896
- Go away!
- What's wrong with you?!

127
00:11:59,920 --> 00:12:01,880
- Are you okay, Sailom?
- Go away! Don't touch me!

128
00:12:02,440 --> 00:12:03,800
- Take it easy.
- Get away from me!

129
00:12:07,440 --> 00:12:09,240
Please step back. I'm a doctor.

130
00:12:09,640 --> 00:12:12,120
Give him some space.

131
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:14,400
Everyone,

132
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:18,120
please step back.

133
00:12:18,560 --> 00:12:19,880
A little bit more.

134
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:22,000
I'm a doctor. I'll help him.

135
00:12:22,760 --> 00:12:23,760
Mister,

136
00:12:24,880 --> 00:12:26,040
please calm yourself down.

137
00:12:31,080 --> 00:12:32,280
Can you hear me?

138
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:49,240
If you can, let's try breathing together.

139
00:12:49,800 --> 00:12:54,600
Just follow me. Breathe
in, deeply and slowly.

140
00:12:55,840 --> 00:12:58,120
And breathe out, long and slow.

141
00:13:00,840 --> 00:13:01,840
Gently now.

142
00:13:02,280 --> 00:13:03,600
Now, place one hand...

143
00:13:04,920 --> 00:13:06,640
right here on your stomach.

144
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:10,000
Feel it rise as you breathe in.

145
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,640
And feel it fall as you breathe out.

146
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:21,720
Just stay with your breath.

147
00:13:26,280 --> 00:13:29,000
Don't tell me you're… a doctor.

148
00:13:31,880 --> 00:13:32,880
Yes, I am.

149
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:35,960
Don't…

150
00:13:35,961 --> 00:13:39,000
tell me that... you're a psychiatrist?

151
00:13:42,040 --> 00:13:43,040
You're right.

152
00:13:46,120 --> 00:13:47,120
I'm Nabnueng.

153
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:49,200
What's your name?

154
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:51,000
Sailom.

155
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:53,600
I see.

156
00:13:54,640 --> 00:13:56,360
You handled that well for tonight.

157
00:13:56,840 --> 00:14:00,000
If you feel overwhelmed,
please feel free to stop by my clinic.

158
00:14:01,040 --> 00:14:02,520
At "Term Suk" (The Happiness) Clinic.

159
00:14:04,400 --> 00:14:05,720
Thank you for your help,

160
00:14:07,520 --> 00:14:08,520
Doctor.

161
00:14:34,560 --> 00:14:37,760
Why was it okay when he touched my hand?

162
00:15:00,760 --> 00:15:01,960
I have something to say.

163
00:15:06,560 --> 00:15:07,080
Let's get married...
I'm sorry.

164
00:15:14,280 --> 00:15:15,560
I'm so sorry.

165
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:18,200
I do love you,

166
00:15:19,240 --> 00:15:22,080
but… I just got a new job

167
00:15:23,320 --> 00:15:24,840
and need to move to Vietnam.

168
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:30,400
Let's get everything sorted out
first and then we think about marriage.

169
00:15:32,760 --> 00:15:35,040
Hey, I'll put lots of my photos here,

170
00:15:36,040 --> 00:15:38,760
so you can always think of me.

171
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:33,600
How much longer? I'm in a hurry.

172
00:16:33,960 --> 00:16:37,120
It's almost done. Please have a seat.

173
00:16:38,240 --> 00:16:41,240
It's taking too long! I'll miss my trip!

174
00:16:43,680 --> 00:16:45,520
I'll be as quick as possible.

175
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:48,960
- I'm in a bit of a hurry!
- Right away.

176
00:16:56,760 --> 00:17:04,760
On this day last year, a Bangkok-Chiang Mai
flight crashed while landing.

177
00:17:07,360 --> 00:17:14,719
And sadly, a child
under 10 died in that accident.

178
00:17:14,720 --> 00:17:19,320
We're so sorry for the child's family.

179
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:23,400
Hey there.

180
00:17:28,440 --> 00:17:29,680
Cheer up.

181
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:33,920
It's okay. Take your time.

182
00:17:34,680 --> 00:17:35,720
Thank you.

183
00:17:54,040 --> 00:17:56,640
This ship goes to Koh Larn!

184
00:17:57,720 --> 00:17:58,720
Thank you.

185
00:17:59,560 --> 00:18:00,320
Thank you.

186
00:18:00,321 --> 00:18:01,560
All aboard!

187
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:03,680
Thank you. Please board the boat.

188
00:18:03,960 --> 00:18:05,240
Ticket, please.

189
00:18:05,280 --> 00:18:06,280
Pay your debt, Dindin.

190
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:10,160
Come on, I told you I'll pay soon.

191
00:18:10,720 --> 00:18:12,440
Right now. Pay up.

192
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:18,440
I need to work now. I'll pay it later.

193
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:20,840
Trick me again and I'll kill you.

194
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:22,520
Don't you see there are customers?

195
00:18:22,600 --> 00:18:24,039
Is this ticket for this boat?

196
00:18:24,040 --> 00:18:26,879
Yes, sir. All aboard.

197
00:18:26,880 --> 00:18:29,000
Oh, mister. Here's a giveaway hat.

198
00:18:33,160 --> 00:18:35,560
Whoever has a ticket can
board the boat right away.

199
00:18:47,120 --> 00:18:48,440
What?! He's gone?!

200
00:18:49,280 --> 00:18:52,000
I told you to watch him! Damn it!

201
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:53,840
He's over there!

202
00:18:54,240 --> 00:18:55,240
After him!

203
00:19:28,520 --> 00:19:29,000
What the hell?!

204
00:19:29,120 --> 00:19:30,240
Sorry, sorry.

205
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:34,000
Hey, what's up?

206
00:19:34,040 --> 00:19:35,959
Can you cover for me and sing at the bar?

207
00:19:35,960 --> 00:19:39,199
Fine, send me the time and place.
I can only go after the transfer. Bye.

208
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:40,200
Hey, wait...

209
00:19:48,600 --> 00:19:49,600
Damn.

210
00:19:49,800 --> 00:19:50,920
Where the hell is he?

211
00:19:53,280 --> 00:19:54,280
What are we gonna do?

212
00:19:54,680 --> 00:19:55,920
Should we wait at his bakery?

213
00:19:57,960 --> 00:20:00,400
No need to go there. He's broke anyway.

214
00:20:00,960 --> 00:20:04,560
Find and squeeze the money out of him. He
hasn't even paid the first month interest.

215
00:20:04,920 --> 00:20:07,040
If the boss finds out, I'm dead.

216
00:20:07,320 --> 00:20:09,400
Yeah, he must be around here somewhere.

217
00:20:10,360 --> 00:20:11,360
Let's check over there.

218
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,280
Goddamn brat.

219
00:20:32,280 --> 00:20:34,600
(Baker Needed. Urgent!)

220
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:37,200
Bakery, huh?

221
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:54,000
P'Nabnueng, wake up!
Mom calls you for lunch!

222
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:03,800
What's wrong?

223
00:21:04,760 --> 00:21:08,120
P'Tawan, come and help me here!
P'Nabnueng looks terrible!

224
00:21:11,120 --> 00:21:13,520
Look at him. P'Nabnueng
looks like death warmed over.

225
00:21:18,960 --> 00:21:20,600
Are you okay, bro?

226
00:21:24,960 --> 00:21:26,120
Gimme a sec to be sad.

227
00:21:30,560 --> 00:21:33,560
Yanin doesn't love you, but we still do.

228
00:21:45,560 --> 00:21:46,800
Sleep a bit more.

229
00:21:47,760 --> 00:21:49,720
I'll get some fish from
the market and grill them.

230
00:21:51,640 --> 00:21:53,920
Looksoh, ask Mom to get the stove ready.

231
00:21:54,280 --> 00:21:56,000
Yep, I'll do it right away.

232
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:12,000
I'm gonna pass you.

233
00:22:12,240 --> 00:22:13,240
Pass me if you can.

234
00:22:13,760 --> 00:22:15,000
I beat you twice already.

235
00:22:16,160 --> 00:22:17,280
Just zip it.

236
00:22:20,040 --> 00:22:22,280
Do you think I'm stopping for you?

237
00:22:23,080 --> 00:22:24,080
You're slow.

238
00:22:24,840 --> 00:22:27,880
So what? Who threw
something at me this time?

239
00:22:28,120 --> 00:22:31,360
- Are you okay, Sailom?
- Go away! Don't touch me!

240
00:22:32,520 --> 00:22:34,240
You need to feel the game.

241
00:22:34,320 --> 00:22:36,320
A little silence wouldn't kill you.

242
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:42,800
I think you're too slow, Lemon.

243
00:22:52,040 --> 00:22:53,240
You two…

244
00:22:55,320 --> 00:22:56,560
About last night…

245
00:22:57,920 --> 00:22:59,080
I'm so sorry.

246
00:23:08,040 --> 00:23:09,240
It's okay.

247
00:23:10,560 --> 00:23:12,840
But why were you like that last night?

248
00:23:13,680 --> 00:23:16,920
Yeah, you can tell us your problems.

249
00:23:23,680 --> 00:23:25,040
Thanks a lot…

250
00:23:25,880 --> 00:23:28,320
but… I'm fine, really.

251
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:33,160
Sailom…

252
00:23:40,440 --> 00:23:47,960
We understand if you don't want to tell us.
We just want to understand you better,

253
00:23:49,240 --> 00:23:51,360
so we know what's okay and what's not.

254
00:23:56,760 --> 00:23:57,960
Sorry.

255
00:24:00,720 --> 00:24:02,120
I'm not ready to talk about it.

256
00:24:06,400 --> 00:24:10,080
Hey, didn't you invite
us to eat? I'm starving.

257
00:24:10,400 --> 00:24:14,640
When will you order some food?
Or should I eat your table's legs?

258
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:20,000
What's so funny? Order something.

259
00:24:20,240 --> 00:24:23,960
Okay, I'll do it.
If you're in a hurry, do it yourself.

260
00:24:35,800 --> 00:24:39,600
Fresh seafood here. Come and get it.

261
00:24:40,160 --> 00:24:43,720
Live fish and crabs right here.
Want some, handsome?

262
00:24:44,760 --> 00:24:46,200
How much for a kilo of squid?

263
00:24:46,360 --> 00:24:48,080
300 baht per kilo. How many kilos?

264
00:24:49,640 --> 00:24:51,920
- Is this all that's left?
- Yes, just three left.

265
00:24:52,320 --> 00:24:54,080
- I'll take all three.
- Alright.

266
00:24:55,320 --> 00:24:56,320
Anything else?

267
00:24:57,120 --> 00:24:59,240
- Just squid.
- Alright.

268
00:25:00,040 --> 00:25:01,720
Look at these squid.

269
00:25:03,880 --> 00:25:05,040
Shellfish are fresh here.

270
00:25:05,760 --> 00:25:06,960
Oh, captain.

271
00:25:07,920 --> 00:25:09,680
How do you do?

272
00:25:12,760 --> 00:25:14,360
Yes, I'm okay.

273
00:25:15,360 --> 00:25:17,840
I heard you're not flying anymore.

274
00:25:19,520 --> 00:25:21,520
Yes, I'm not.

275
00:25:26,520 --> 00:25:27,680
How have you been?

276
00:25:28,080 --> 00:25:34,600
After that day, my husband and I
moved here to Pattaya to run a business.

277
00:25:39,760 --> 00:25:40,960
I'm truly sorry.

278
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:44,200
It's okay.

279
00:25:45,280 --> 00:25:47,000
I'm not here to blame you.

280
00:25:55,560 --> 00:25:56,560
Dear…

281
00:25:57,400 --> 00:25:58,400
Look there.

282
00:25:59,240 --> 00:26:01,440
The captain likes squid...

283
00:26:01,520 --> 00:26:03,120
just like our daughter used to.

284
00:26:16,880 --> 00:26:18,040
Thank you.

285
00:26:25,600 --> 00:26:26,640
Here.

286
00:26:28,520 --> 00:26:29,520
Thanks.

287
00:26:47,200 --> 00:26:48,200
Hey.

288
00:26:49,280 --> 00:26:50,280
Why are you spacing out?

289
00:26:51,080 --> 00:26:52,080
It's nothing.

290
00:26:56,920 --> 00:26:58,080
Where's Sky?

291
00:26:59,400 --> 00:27:00,640
Working, maybe?

292
00:27:04,160 --> 00:27:07,000
He's been busy lately.
Been out since this morning.

293
00:27:07,840 --> 00:27:09,000
Meeting with customers.

294
00:27:24,240 --> 00:27:25,440
Feel better, dear?

295
00:27:28,120 --> 00:27:29,120
Yes, Mom.

296
00:27:30,760 --> 00:27:35,240
That's life. Nothing's certain at all.

297
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:39,000
You're right.

298
00:27:39,600 --> 00:27:42,240
Still heartbroken, bro?

299
00:27:43,600 --> 00:27:44,600
Yep.

300
00:27:45,520 --> 00:27:47,920
Now I get what it feels like to be dumped.

301
00:27:50,960 --> 00:27:52,760
She's been stringing
you along all this time.

302
00:27:54,760 --> 00:27:55,760
I know.

303
00:27:59,040 --> 00:28:00,840
But when seeing it for myself...

304
00:28:02,920 --> 00:28:04,040
I'm just lost.

305
00:28:06,920 --> 00:28:10,800
Yeah… give it some time, doctor.

306
00:28:16,320 --> 00:28:18,520
Even a psychiatrist needs his mom's care.

307
00:28:19,680 --> 00:28:23,560
Look who's talking, Tawan.
Don't think I don't know.

308
00:28:23,920 --> 00:28:28,160
It's okay to tell me if something's
upsetting you. Don't be shy.

309
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:30,920
What? I'm fine!

310
00:28:31,400 --> 00:28:32,400
Yeah, right.

311
00:28:35,560 --> 00:28:37,040
Alright, let's have a toast!

312
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:42,000
Okay, cheers!

313
00:28:44,000 --> 00:28:45,320
Bottoms up, shall we?

314
00:28:48,080 --> 00:28:50,760
- Are you sure, Mom?
- Look at your brother.

315
00:29:00,120 --> 00:29:01,320
I'm sorry…

316
00:29:03,800 --> 00:29:05,680
I couldn't help you at all.

317
00:29:22,920 --> 00:29:23,920
Hey, Ben.

318
00:29:24,280 --> 00:29:27,520
I almost got my ass kicked
by the debt collectors today.

319
00:29:28,560 --> 00:29:29,760
They were hunting me down.

320
00:29:30,560 --> 00:29:33,280
Didn't you say you
transfer the money today?

321
00:29:33,920 --> 00:29:38,880
Don't give me that crap! I saw your IG!
You took a girl out for omakase!

322
00:29:40,640 --> 00:29:45,680
Borrowing was easy for you.
Don't make returning it so damn hard.

323
00:29:46,320 --> 00:29:49,360
Send me the money now,
or you'll deal with me.

324
00:29:51,160 --> 00:29:52,160
Ben?

325
00:29:53,080 --> 00:29:54,080
Hello?

326
00:29:55,040 --> 00:29:56,440
You bastard.

327
00:30:03,160 --> 00:30:04,520
Damn it!

328
00:30:04,720 --> 00:30:06,080
Ouch! Who did this?!

329
00:30:07,400 --> 00:30:08,560
Was it you?

330
00:30:10,040 --> 00:30:11,320
What's your problem?

331
00:30:12,400 --> 00:30:14,120
What the hell is wrong with you?

332
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:16,000
You brat.

333
00:30:19,040 --> 00:30:20,640
Bastard.

334
00:30:22,280 --> 00:30:23,520
You started it.

335
00:30:23,840 --> 00:30:25,000
You want a piece of me?

336
00:30:25,160 --> 00:30:26,400
What if I do?

337
00:30:26,760 --> 00:30:27,760
Take this.

338
00:30:41,440 --> 00:30:42,440
Fine.

339
00:31:26,240 --> 00:31:28,240
Does it have to be this early, Mom?

340
00:31:29,320 --> 00:31:34,200
Keeping busy is good. It'll help
take your mind off your heartbreak.

341
00:31:35,920 --> 00:31:37,640
I'm not that heartbroken.

342
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:39,920
This is the best way.

343
00:31:40,400 --> 00:31:42,120
Here, deliver this drink.

344
00:31:42,680 --> 00:31:44,280
I've sent you the address.

345
00:31:46,600 --> 00:31:47,840
It's not that far.

346
00:31:48,400 --> 00:31:51,240
Yes, now hurry, or it'll get cold.

347
00:31:51,920 --> 00:31:53,240
- Okay, Mom.
- See you.

348
00:32:16,720 --> 00:32:18,720
How long will you be
at Chiangmai this time?

349
00:32:19,120 --> 00:32:20,120
Maybe…

350
00:32:20,560 --> 00:32:21,680
a week?

351
00:32:22,440 --> 00:32:23,840
I'll buy sai oua for you.

352
00:32:24,680 --> 00:32:25,200
Okay.

353
00:32:25,520 --> 00:32:27,200
Have a safe trip, Dad.

354
00:32:27,800 --> 00:32:29,080
Call me when you're there.

355
00:32:29,840 --> 00:32:30,840
Of course.

356
00:32:51,320 --> 00:32:52,880
Yes, Mom?

357
00:32:53,600 --> 00:32:57,400
How's everything in
Pattaya? Are you doing okay?

358
00:32:59,360 --> 00:33:00,600
I'm good, Mom.

359
00:33:01,080 --> 00:33:04,160
You're alright staying by yourself?

360
00:33:05,800 --> 00:33:07,960
Of course, Mom.

361
00:33:08,000 --> 00:33:09,200
But…

362
00:33:09,640 --> 00:33:10,640
Mom…

363
00:33:11,200 --> 00:33:16,400
don't worry. I'm grown up now.
I can take care of myself.

364
00:33:17,040 --> 00:33:22,440
Right. If there's something wrong,
you can call me anytime. Okay?

365
00:33:22,640 --> 00:33:23,640
Alright.

366
00:33:24,240 --> 00:33:25,360
I gotta go.

367
00:33:25,720 --> 00:33:27,960
Okay. I love you, dear.

368
00:33:28,160 --> 00:33:29,640
I love you too, Mom.

369
00:33:38,880 --> 00:33:40,040
Hello!

370
00:33:40,560 --> 00:33:41,880
"Love Like a Bike" delivery here.

371
00:33:50,800 --> 00:33:52,000
Oh, doctor.

372
00:33:52,920 --> 00:33:54,080
Oh, Sailom.

373
00:33:55,880 --> 00:34:00,960
You're a doctor. Buy why…
are you delivering coffee?

374
00:34:01,200 --> 00:34:05,840
Oh, it's my family's café.
I help out at the café after my day job.

375
00:34:06,800 --> 00:34:08,000
Here's your coffee.

376
00:34:08,680 --> 00:34:09,840
The payment's been processed.

377
00:34:10,200 --> 00:34:11,400
Okay, thank you.

378
00:34:18,240 --> 00:34:19,920
Go away! Don't touch me!

379
00:34:20,720 --> 00:34:21,920
Why was it okay…

380
00:34:24,200 --> 00:34:26,240
when he touched my hand?

381
00:34:37,840 --> 00:34:39,000
Don't hurt me!

382
00:34:39,040 --> 00:34:40,240
Mom, help me!

383
00:34:43,440 --> 00:34:44,440
No!

384
00:34:46,200 --> 00:34:47,400
Don't hurt me.

385
00:34:48,800 --> 00:34:50,000
Get out!

386
00:34:56,600 --> 00:34:57,840
Sailom.

387
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:02,160
It's okay.

388
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:04,160
Stay with me.

389
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:08,200
Breathe in deeply.

390
00:35:27,440 --> 00:35:29,520
I'm… sorry.

391
00:35:32,560 --> 00:35:34,560
It's totally fine.

392
00:35:59,520 --> 00:36:00,599
Oh.

393
00:36:00,600 --> 00:36:02,320
Sailom.

394
00:36:03,680 --> 00:36:05,120
Put this shirt on quickly.

395
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:08,160
Thank you.

396
00:36:23,720 --> 00:36:28,160
By the way, I ordered you new coffee.
I'll bring it over to you soon.

397
00:36:28,600 --> 00:36:30,360
It's okay. I spilled it.

398
00:36:31,320 --> 00:36:32,320
Well…

399
00:36:32,680 --> 00:36:34,200
I'll wash and return your shirt later.

400
00:36:34,400 --> 00:36:36,960
Don't worry. I can wash it myself.

401
00:36:37,160 --> 00:36:39,000
Please, I insist.

402
00:36:39,280 --> 00:36:40,320
It's totally fine.

403
00:36:40,720 --> 00:36:41,840
It's really okay.

404
00:36:43,400 --> 00:36:45,200
Don't you have other places to deliver?

405
00:36:46,000 --> 00:36:47,160
There's no orders now.

406
00:36:54,440 --> 00:36:55,680
Can I ask you a qquestion?

407
00:36:57,000 --> 00:36:58,160
How many jobs do you have?

408
00:36:59,520 --> 00:37:03,840
Not many. Just the clinic and the café.

409
00:37:06,840 --> 00:37:09,160
Feel free to visit the café.

410
00:37:09,800 --> 00:37:11,040
Coffee's on me.

411
00:37:17,360 --> 00:37:19,800
I'll borrow your pen.

412
00:37:35,600 --> 00:37:38,520
"This man can have everything for free.
From Doctor Nabnueng."

413
00:37:44,360 --> 00:37:46,040
Thank you, doctor.

414
00:37:46,840 --> 00:37:47,960
You're welcome.

415
00:37:59,120 --> 00:38:00,320
Yes, Mom?

416
00:38:00,640 --> 00:38:03,760
Nabnueng, can you
deliver another cup for me?

417
00:38:04,120 --> 00:38:05,760
Right away, Mom.

418
00:38:08,000 --> 00:38:09,000
I've got to go now.

419
00:38:09,560 --> 00:38:10,560
Alright.

420
00:38:32,360 --> 00:38:35,240
It reeks of coffee now.

421
00:38:36,400 --> 00:38:37,680
Can I get this stain out?

422
00:38:46,920 --> 00:38:47,520
Hey.

423
00:38:47,880 --> 00:38:48,960
You can't be serious.

424
00:38:49,360 --> 00:38:53,000
There are many places to go in Pattaya,
but you chose to come here?

425
00:38:53,400 --> 00:38:55,600
Don't they have cafés in the US?

426
00:38:56,200 --> 00:38:58,280
I just got back. Spoil me a little.

427
00:38:58,760 --> 00:39:02,080
Don't you want to chill out on an island?

428
00:39:03,080 --> 00:39:06,320
We can go later. The summer's long anyway.

429
00:39:08,880 --> 00:39:10,040
Here's your receipt.

430
00:39:11,320 --> 00:39:12,560
Thank you.

431
00:39:14,880 --> 00:39:17,600
Are you on vacation?
I've never seen you before.

432
00:39:17,800 --> 00:39:20,120
I'm a local, but this
is my first time here.

433
00:39:20,680 --> 00:39:24,600
My friend just came back
from the US and took us here.

434
00:39:25,840 --> 00:39:27,320
Did you read reviews from somewhere?

435
00:39:27,840 --> 00:39:29,000
Not at all.

436
00:39:29,880 --> 00:39:31,680
I only want to use this.

437
00:39:32,920 --> 00:39:33,920
Here.

438
00:39:36,560 --> 00:39:37,720
Oh…

439
00:39:38,200 --> 00:39:39,520
you're P'Sailom, right?

440
00:39:40,000 --> 00:39:42,680
P'Nabnueng mentioned you.
Everything's on the house today.

441
00:39:43,040 --> 00:39:45,000
Just a cup of coffee is enough.

442
00:39:45,400 --> 00:39:46,400
I can pay for the rest.

443
00:39:46,680 --> 00:39:49,280
Don't worry.
P'Nabnueng said you all can eat for free.

444
00:39:56,000 --> 00:39:59,400
Tell Doctor Nabnueng
that I say "thank you."

445
00:40:02,760 --> 00:40:03,760
Isn't…

446
00:40:04,040 --> 00:40:05,400
Doctor Nabnueng here?

447
00:40:05,520 --> 00:40:09,040
He works at his clinic today.
It's not far from here.

448
00:40:09,320 --> 00:40:10,800
I see…

449
00:40:12,080 --> 00:40:15,520
Please stop by tomorrow.
We'll have baked goods again.

450
00:40:16,280 --> 00:40:17,280
Alright.

451
00:40:18,200 --> 00:40:20,520
Excuse me, can I have a menu?

452
00:40:23,073 --> 00:40:28,273
Wait. Doctor Nabnueng?
Is he the guy who took your necklace?

453
00:40:28,680 --> 00:40:30,000
When did you get close to him?

454
00:40:34,560 --> 00:40:36,720
Come. Let's go somewhere else.

455
00:40:55,880 --> 00:40:59,080
Let's split up here. I've
got something to do.

456
00:40:59,400 --> 00:41:00,400
Wait…

457
00:41:00,680 --> 00:41:06,920
What's this? You invited us here, then want
to leave, and now you've got something to do?

458
00:41:07,080 --> 00:41:08,160
You're suspicious.

459
00:41:10,720 --> 00:41:11,920
It's nothing much!

460
00:41:12,880 --> 00:41:16,000
I just wanted you two to try coffee here.

461
00:41:17,400 --> 00:41:19,720
How did you get that "name card?"

462
00:41:19,880 --> 00:41:24,000
When did you get close to that doctor?
Didn't you two fight that night?

463
00:41:25,800 --> 00:41:27,040
His name is Nabnueng!

464
00:41:27,600 --> 00:41:29,960
I asked when you two get close.

465
00:41:32,640 --> 00:41:33,640
Well…

466
00:41:34,520 --> 00:41:35,720
not that close.

467
00:41:36,440 --> 00:41:41,680
Yesterday, Doctor Nabnueng delivered
coffee to my house and I spilled it.

468
00:41:42,560 --> 00:41:48,400
He gave me the card with his
signature to make up for it. That's all.

469
00:41:49,640 --> 00:41:50,960
Really?!

470
00:41:52,000 --> 00:41:53,000
Yep!

471
00:41:54,040 --> 00:41:55,160
Do you like him?

472
00:41:56,320 --> 00:41:59,520
Come on! I only just met him!

473
00:42:00,080 --> 00:42:01,440
It's love at first sight.

474
00:42:03,840 --> 00:42:05,760
I'm done talking with you guys.

475
00:42:06,880 --> 00:42:08,040
I'm out of here.

476
00:42:11,013 --> 00:42:12,612
What's next?

477
00:42:13,000 --> 00:42:15,400
Let's just go home. Your house, my house.

478
00:42:16,240 --> 00:42:17,960
- Come.
- Okay.

479
00:42:26,920 --> 00:42:29,880
Mom, I have some gossip.

480
00:42:30,080 --> 00:42:32,520
"This man can have everything for free.
From Doctor Nabnueng."

481
00:42:33,400 --> 00:42:35,400
Oh, who's this?

482
00:42:35,680 --> 00:42:39,960
He's P'Sailom from the US.
P'Nabnueng can finally move on.

483
00:42:40,840 --> 00:42:43,520
- Isn't it too soon?
- Not at all.

484
00:42:45,600 --> 00:42:47,760
I'd better text P'Nabnueng.

485
00:42:48,720 --> 00:42:49,720
Mom,

486
00:42:50,320 --> 00:42:53,280
when is the 'yummy treat' baker coming?

487
00:42:54,953 --> 00:42:56,753
He'll be here soon.

488
00:42:59,240 --> 00:43:00,319
Good afternoon, Mrs. Phailin.

489
00:43:00,320 --> 00:43:02,040
Oh, Dindin. You're here.

490
00:43:03,080 --> 00:43:05,520
I prepared the ingredients.
Let's get started.

491
00:43:05,600 --> 00:43:07,120
Yes, right away.

492
00:43:08,080 --> 00:43:10,920
Tawan! Come here!

493
00:43:11,360 --> 00:43:12,600
What is it, Mom?!

494
00:43:29,800 --> 00:43:31,000
You brat.

495
00:43:32,440 --> 00:43:33,240
You started it.
You want a piece of me?

496
00:43:34,720 --> 00:43:36,000
What if I do?

497
00:43:41,800 --> 00:43:43,960
Good afternoon, P'Tawan.

498
00:44:20,240 --> 00:44:21,319
Hello.

499
00:44:21,320 --> 00:44:23,160
Do you have an appointment?

500
00:44:24,400 --> 00:44:26,800
Ah, no... I don't.

501
00:44:27,440 --> 00:44:29,280
I'm actually to see Dr.Nubnueng.

502
00:44:29,960 --> 00:44:30,960
Oh,

503
00:44:31,360 --> 00:44:35,120
he's out for field work today.

504
00:44:35,400 --> 00:44:36,400
Field work?

505
00:44:36,800 --> 00:44:37,800
Yes.

506
00:45:01,000 --> 00:45:02,160
Sailom?

507
00:45:05,160 --> 00:45:06,160
What brings you here?

508
00:45:07,920 --> 00:45:12,040
Oh... I was just passing by.

509
00:45:13,280 --> 00:45:16,400
What about you? What are you doing here?

510
00:45:18,360 --> 00:45:20,600
I'm out doing field work
with the SWING Foundation.

511
00:45:21,240 --> 00:45:23,400
Providing counseling for nightlife workers.

512
00:45:23,880 --> 00:45:26,760
They deserve the same
protections as everyone else.

513
00:45:27,800 --> 00:45:29,000
I see.

514
00:45:29,680 --> 00:45:32,440
I thought you only saw
patients at the clinic.

515
00:45:33,160 --> 00:45:34,720
I didn't expect to see you out here.

516
00:45:35,360 --> 00:45:36,880
I just want to help out however I can.

517
00:45:42,600 --> 00:45:43,600
Are you hungry?

518
00:45:44,280 --> 00:45:45,280
Huh?

519
00:45:46,000 --> 00:45:47,000
Hungry for what?

520
00:45:47,360 --> 00:45:50,040
Hungry for dinner. Want to go grab a bite?

521
00:46:12,680 --> 00:46:14,536
(Next Episode)
Take it slow, or you'll get drunk.

522
00:46:14,560 --> 00:46:15,600
I'm fine, Doc.

523
00:46:16,240 --> 00:46:17,720
I can handle this much.

524
00:46:17,840 --> 00:46:21,320
This is my first time.
Didn't know it'd... feel this good.

525
00:46:21,440 --> 00:46:22,760
Do you like it?

526
00:46:23,160 --> 00:46:24,160
I do.

527
00:46:25,040 --> 00:46:28,640
Seriously, have you ever even
baked before? I don't think you have.

528
00:46:28,840 --> 00:46:31,160
If you're an expert, do it yourself.

529
00:46:31,760 --> 00:46:32,760
Oh, no…

530
00:46:33,600 --> 00:46:35,880
Don't tell me the Doctor…

